<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Blog on Dave Pereira</title><link>https://davepereira.co.uk/blog/</link><description>Recent content in Blog on Dave Pereira</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Fri, 14 Mar 2025 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://davepereira.co.uk/blog/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Markdown Syntax Guide</title><link>https://davepereira.co.uk/blog/markdown-syntax/</link><pubDate>Fri, 14 Mar 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://davepereira.co.uk/blog/markdown-syntax/</guid><description>&lt;p>This article offers a sample of basic Markdown syntax that can be used in Hugo content files, also it shows whether basic HTML elements are decorated with CSS in a Hugo theme.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Placeholder Text</title><link>https://davepereira.co.uk/blog/placeholder-text/</link><pubDate>Thu, 13 Mar 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://davepereira.co.uk/blog/placeholder-text/</guid><description>&lt;p>Lorem est tota propiore conpellat pectoribus de pectora summo.&lt;/p></description></item><item><title>Rich Content</title><link>https://davepereira.co.uk/blog/rich-content/</link><pubDate>Thu, 13 Mar 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://davepereira.co.uk/blog/rich-content/</guid><description>&lt;p>Hugo ships with several &lt;a href="https://gohugo.io/content-management/shortcodes/#use-hugos-built-in-shortcodes" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Built-in Shortcodes&lt;/a>
 for rich content, along with a &lt;a href="https://gohugo.io/about/hugo-and-gdpr/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Privacy Config&lt;/a>
 and a set of Simple Shortcodes that enable static and no-JS versions of various social media embeds.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="heading">&lt;/h2></description></item><item><title>Math Typesetting</title><link>https://davepereira.co.uk/blog/math-typesetting/</link><pubDate>Fri, 07 Mar 2025 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://davepereira.co.uk/blog/math-typesetting/</guid><description>&lt;p>The theme now supports server side rendering of math equations via hugo&amp;rsquo;s built-in KaTeX rendering engine.
No manual activation is needed, you can start using LaTeX math expressions in your Markdown content right away.&lt;/p>
&lt;h3 id="prerequisites">Prerequisites&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>Please enable and configure the &lt;a href="https://gohugo.io/configuration/markup/#passthrough" target="_blank" rel="noopener">passthrough extension&lt;/a>
 in the Hugo configuration file:&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight" filename="hugo.yaml">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#282a36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-yaml" data-lang="yaml">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#ff79c6">markup&lt;/span>:
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#ff79c6">goldmark&lt;/span>:
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#ff79c6">extensions&lt;/span>:
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#ff79c6">passthrough&lt;/span>:
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#ff79c6">delimiters&lt;/span>:
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#ff79c6">block&lt;/span>: [[&lt;span style="color:#f1fa8c">&amp;#39;\[&amp;#39;&lt;/span>, &lt;span style="color:#f1fa8c">&amp;#39;\]&amp;#39;&lt;/span>], [&lt;span style="color:#f1fa8c">&amp;#39;$$&amp;#39;&lt;/span>, &lt;span style="color:#f1fa8c">&amp;#39;$$&amp;#39;&lt;/span>]]
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#ff79c6">inline&lt;/span>: [[&lt;span style="color:#f1fa8c">&amp;#39;\(&amp;#39;&lt;/span>, &lt;span style="color:#f1fa8c">&amp;#39;\)&amp;#39;&lt;/span>]]
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span> &lt;span style="color:#ff79c6">enable&lt;/span>: &lt;span style="color:#ff79c6">true&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h3 id="examples">Examples&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>Both inline and separate paragraph LaTeX math expressions are supported in the Markdown content.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>